The TABmate Closure analysis assumes that your TAB file
 follows a naming convention for equations:
 the equation which explains variable "p1", say, should be named "E_p1" (prefix E_).
 See the online help for more details (menu item Tools...Help on Tools).

 Search this report for the characters "!?" to find problems.

Report is divided into the following sections:
Section 1. Directly matching equations and variables
Section 2. Matching equations and variables (many equations to 1 variable)
Section 3. Unmatched equations (should be none)
Section 4. Unmatched variables (potential exogenous list)
Section 5. Backsolved, substituted and omitted variables
Section 6. Condensation suggestions
Section 7. Tally of variables and equations
Section 8. Strangely named variables (possible error)


