         tpdall  COMM*REG   comm.-, source-spec. shifter in private cons. tax of dom. c
         tpmall  COMM*REG   comm.-, source-spec. shifter in private cons. tax of imp. c



Section 6. Condensation suggestions
***********************************

You might consider either backsolving or substituting
  the following variables and equations, if they have more than 5000 components.
Include in your CMF file a statement like:
  Condensation information file = cond.txt ;
to generate a report identifying the largest equations (which usually ought to be backsolved or substituted).
Very large variables should be substituted, not backsolved.
Text below is formatted so you can paste straight into the STI file:

! Variable       Size

B   !  backsolve
peb ! ENDW*ACTS*REG
E_peb
B   !  backsolve
pebfactreal ! ENDWMS*REG
E_pebfactreal
B   !  backsolve
pefactreal ! ENDWMS*REG
E_pefactreal
B   !  backsolve
pms ! COMM*REG
E_pms
B   !  backsolve
qc ! COMM*REG
E_qc
B   !  backsolve
qca ! COMM*ACTS*REG
E_qca
B   !  backsolve
qds ! COMM*REG
E_qds
B   !  backsolve
qms ! COMM*REG
E_qms
B   !  backsolve
qo ! ACTS*REG
E_qo

GEMPACK 8.0 and later allows you to specify backsolves
  directly in the TAB file, in the following format:

Backsolve peb using E_peb;                 ! ENDW*ACTS*REG !
Backsolve pebfactreal using E_pebfactreal; ! ENDWMS*REG !
Backsolve pefactreal using E_pefactreal;   ! ENDWMS*REG !
Backsolve pms using E_pms;                 ! COMM*REG !
Backsolve qc using E_qc;                   ! COMM*REG !
Backsolve qca using E_qca;                 ! COMM*ACTS*REG !
Backsolve qds using E_qds;                 ! COMM*REG !
Backsolve qms using E_qms;                 ! COMM*REG !
Backsolve qo using E_qo;                   ! ACTS*REG !

You might consider omitting the following variables.
Omitting a variable is equivalent to assuming that it is exogenous and unshocked.
Text below is formatted so you can paste straight into the STI file:

o          ! omit following variables
afall            ! ALLF*ACTS*REG
afeall           ! ENDW*ACTS*REG
ams              ! COMM*REG*REG
aoall            ! ACTS*REG
endwslack        ! ENDW*REG
profitslack      ! ACTS*REG
qe               ! ENDWMS*REG
qesf             ! ENDWF*ACTS*REG
tinc             ! ENDW*ACTS*REG
tm               ! COMM*REG
tms              ! COMM*REG*REG
to               ! COMM*ACTS*REG
tradslack        ! COMM*REG
tx               ! COMM*REG
txs              ! COMM*REG*REG
                  ! empty line signals end of omissions list

GEMPACK 8.0 and later allows you to specify omissions
  directly in the TAB file, in the following format:

Omit afall;       ! ALLF*ACTS*REG !
Omit afeall;      ! ENDW*ACTS*REG !
Omit ams;         ! COMM*REG*REG !
Omit aoall;       ! ACTS*REG !
Omit endwslack;   ! ENDW*REG !
Omit profitslack; ! ACTS*REG !
Omit qe;          ! ENDWMS*REG !
Omit qesf;        ! ENDWF*ACTS*REG !
Omit tinc;        ! ENDW*ACTS*REG !
Omit tm;          ! COMM*REG !
Omit tms;         ! COMM*REG*REG !
Omit to;          ! COMM*ACTS*REG !
Omit tradslack;   ! COMM*REG !
Omit tx;          ! COMM*REG !
Omit txs;         ! COMM*REG*REG !


