Section 8. Strangely named variables (possible error)
*****************************************************

By convention, names of ordinary change variables are usually uppercase,
or begin with "D" or "c_" or "cont" or "cnt".
Following variables do NOT follow this convention:

      Variable 

           dpav  is a percent change variable named like an ordinary change variable
         dpavev  is a percent change variable named like an ordinary change variable
          dpgov  is a percent change variable named like an ordinary change variable
         dppriv  is a percent change variable named like an ordinary change variable
         dpsave  is a percent change variable named like an ordinary change variable
          dpsum  is a percent change variable named like an ordinary change variable

